    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to Tamás Nádasdy (Vienna, 26 May 1552)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">The councillors of the Chamber are making a mistake when
                            they are not sending Tamás Nádasdy his money when they should. Maurice,
                            Elector of Saxony has occupied Udine through deceit, forgetting about
                            his faith and office; the Emperor still holds Ulm and Augsburg. Albert
                            Alcibiades has accepted the capitulation of Nuremberg, he is said to
                            have burned down the surrounding area almost completely. The French King
                            advanced to Speyer, but when he heard there that a city in Lorraine was
                            under attack, he retreated to liberate that city. When the Emperor heard
                            about the occupation of Udine, he traveled to Bruneck. The King is
                            accompanying the Bishop of Trento to Padua, and they are expecting
                            Maurice to come there to negotiate.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Servitiorum meorum commendationem, Spectabilis Magnifice Domine et
                    Frater Observandissime! </p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Domini camerarii male habeant, quod <choice>
                        <orig><gap extent="unknown" reason="damage" unit="word"/>niam</orig>
                        <supplied><corr>pecu</corr>niam</supplied>
                    </choice> Dominationi Vestrae non miserint, <choice>
                        <orig><gap extent="unknown" reason="damage" unit="word"/>ent</orig>
                        <supplied><corr>deb</corr>ent</supplied>
                    </choice> tamen, si vera sunt, quae dicunt. <choice>
                        <orig><gap extent="unknown" reason="damage" unit="word"/>ova</orig>
                        <supplied><corr>N</corr>ova</supplied>
                    </choice> haec sunt. <persName>Dux Mauritius</persName><note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.1">Maurice, Elector of Saxony.</note><choice>
                        <orig>f<gap extent="unknown" reason="damage" unit="word"/>i</orig>
                        <supplied>f<corr>ide</corr>i</supplied>
                    </choice> et officii sui immemor, <placeName>Clusam</placeName><note
                        type="critic" xml:id="note.2">Probably Udine.</note> arcem regiae maiestatis
                    ad ostium Tyrolis versus <placeName>Augustam</placeName><note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.3">Augsburg.</note> existentem astu nuper accepit,
                        <placeName>Ulma</placeName> et <placeName>Argentina</placeName><note
                        type="critic" xml:id="note.4">Strasbourg.</note> strenue et constanter in
                    fide caesaris permansit. <persName>Marchio Albertus</persName><note
                        type="critic" xml:id="note.5">Albert Alcibiades, Margrave of
                        Brandenburg-Kulmbach (1522–1557).</note> nebulo ille et omnium bonorum
                    suorum decoctor <choice>
                        <orig>civit<gap extent="unknown" reason="damage" unit="word"/>em</orig>
                        <supplied>civit<corr>at</corr>em</supplied>
                    </choice> quandam Newrembergensium per <choice>
                        <orig><gap extent="unknown" reason="damage" unit="word"/>ditionem</orig>
                        <supplied><corr>de</corr>ditionem</supplied>
                    </choice> accepit. Dicunt eum <choice>
                        <orig>alio<gap extent="unknown" reason="damage" unit="word"/></orig>
                        <supplied>alio<corr>qui</corr></supplied>
                    </choice> suburbii civitatis quoque Newrembergensis <choice>
                        <orig>p<gap extent="unknown" reason="damage" unit="word"/></orig>
                        <supplied>p<corr>aene</corr></supplied>
                    </choice> combussisse. <persName>Rex Galliae</persName><note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.6">Francis I of France.</note><choice>
                        <orig><gap extent="unknown" reason="damage" unit="word"/>gressus</orig>
                        <supplied><corr>in</corr>gressus</supplied>
                    </choice> fuit <placeName>Spyram</placeName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.7"
                        >Speier.</note> usque. <choice>
                        <orig>Illin<gap extent="unknown" reason="damage" unit="word"/></orig>
                        <supplied>Illin<corr>c</corr></supplied>
                    </choice> audita obsidione cuiusdam <choice>
                        <orig>civi<gap extent="unknown" reason="damage" unit="word"/>s</orig>
                        <supplied>civi<corr>tati</corr>s</supplied>
                    </choice> in Lotharingia, quam in manibus suis habet per exercitum Flandricum
                    serenissimae reginae facta et etiam unius vel alterius civitatis occupatione
                    penes <placeName>Rhenum</placeName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.8">Rhine
                        river.</note> retrocessisse dicitur, ad liberandam ab obsidione civitatem
                    illam. <persName>Maiestas caesarea</persName> audita
                        <placeName>Clusae</placeName> captione, profecta est ad civitatem quandam
                    cuius nomen nunc non succurrit, <add corresp="Olahus" type="insert">opinor
                        Prawnek</add>.<note type="critic" xml:id="note.9"
                    >Bruneck.</note><!--<persName/>-->Tridentini <choice>
                        <orig><gap extent="1" reason="damage" unit="word"/>dinalis</orig>
                        <supplied><corr>car</corr>dinalis</supplied>
                    </choice><note type="critic" xml:id="note.10">Cristoforo Madruzzo (1512–1578)
                        studied at the University of Padua and Bologna. He first received the
                        canonry at Trento in 1529. In 1536, he was Canon of Salzburg, in 1537 Canon
                        of Brixen, and following Bernhard von Cles’s death, he earned the
                        archiepiscopate of Trento, see <hi rend="smallcap">Becker</hi>,
                        2006.</note><milestone unit="pb"/> ad <placeName>Brixinam</placeName>,<note
                        type="critic" xml:id="note.11">Brixen.</note> quattuor millionibus
                    distantium <del corresp="Olahus">profecta est</del> maiestas regia comitata est
                    eum aliquamdiu, et hodie, uti credimus, constituetur
                        <placeName>Patavii</placeName>.<note type="critic" xml:id="note.12"
                        >Padua.</note> Exspectamus <persName>Mauritium</persName> et alios eo, si
                    venerint ad tractatus faciendos. <del corresp="Olahus">Dux Ioannes</del> Illic
                    sua maiestas mox revertetur. <persName>Dux Ioannes</persName> captivus Saxoniae
                    est <gap extent="1" reason="illegible" unit="word"/> donatus est tamen in curam
                    caesaris. Haec sunt, quae habeo. Dominatio Vestra feliciter valeat.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.3">Ex <placeName>Vienna</placeName> 26. Maii 1552.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.4">
                    <seg type="signature">Frater et servitor Agriensis etc. manu propria</seg>
                </p>
                <p xml:id="p.5">Serenissimus <persName>Maximilianus</persName> rex de rebus
                    nonnullis nuntiavit per dominum <persName>Bathyany</persName><note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.13">Kristóf Batthyány.</note> Dominationi Vestrae. Ad has
                    exspectamus responsum.</p>
                <pb/>
            </div>
            <div style="handwritten" type="verso" xml:id="d.2">
                <head>On the outer side:</head>
                <p xml:id="p.6">Spectabili et magnifico domino Thomae de Nadasd, comiti perpetuo
                    terrae Fogaras, iudici curiae regiae maiestatis et supremo regni capitaneo etc.
                    domino et fratri observandissimo.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.7">Ad manus proprias.</p>
            </div>
